                    <div class="text post">
	
                        
                            <h2>With Two Sets of Lungs</h2>
                        

                        <p>A belt of midnight and dead stars, for centuries still gleaming, and I&rsquo;m happy to be alive. I&rsquo;m alive in the month swathed in spiced air and shared sheets. Delana&rsquo;s name shining like a cymbal at the base of my throat. I&rsquo;m alive watching it course swingsets around the room, followed by my breath&rsquo;s burnt dusk. And I&rsquo;m alive in her sweet laugh, in the strange accents she deploys at any given moment, in her before-bed routines, and I&rsquo;m alive in her sadness too. Here under the moon, there aches an old lachrymose light, lime green, and its just like a weekend spent on Long Island. I hear the hurried hush of a closing diner, brooms brushing, sleep waiting; I can hear Delana dreaming in my bed; I can see the sad smiles of my parents trying to make love work again. Here, it hurts in the same happy way too.</p><p>The street below is the real world, and people blink in the darkness like the springing notes of a piano. At this height, it&rsquo;s the roar that truly sings to me, the deep roar of a giant snoring beneath the earth&rsquo;s surface. A searing branch of stars combs my heart into the night. The time took my body away from me, and here I am, still alive in this dirtiness. I think my love sometimes sounds like the voice of a little boy. Everything else is&ndash; well&hellip; still everything else. It sometimes takes the youngest part of me to know what&rsquo;s real.</p>
						
						<div class="postmeta"><a href="http://thenatureofdaylight.tumblr.com/post/153029353682/with-two-sets-of-lungs">3 weeks ago</a>&nbsp; <a href="http://thenatureofdaylight.tumblr.com/post/153029353682/with-two-sets-of-lungs" style="text-transform:lowercase;">Notes (3)</a></div>

