                            <h2>Drowned in the Eye of the Equinox</h2>
                        

                        <p>The moon&rsquo;s poem: my eyes rotate<br>
around to reproach my<br>
insides.<br>
The pith&rsquo;s fumes sing <i>love me</i><br>
sharing no name but<br>a harmony,<br>
and it&rsquo;s truly October again, <br>
worn as an emblem<br>
of resurrection.</p><p>Pines and oaks slowly thin,<br>
like heartstrings chiseling<br>
a cinereal sheet, <br>
shadow spilling<br>
over. <br>
Cold rainwaters descend<br>
down black tongues<br>
till tomorrow, with<br>
crickets kept.</p><p>Our world dies a beautiful mammal,<br>
breathing<br>
sleeping<br>and I&rsquo;m careful tonight,<br>
fire extinguished: a crying child,<br>a seed.</p>
						
						<div class="postmeta"><a href="http://thenatureofdaylight.tumblr.com/post/151389542947/drowned-in-the-eye-of-the-equinox">1 month ago</a>&nbsp; <a href="http://thenatureofdaylight.tumblr.com/post/151389542947/drowned-in-the-eye-of-the-equinox" style="text-transform:lowercase;">Notes (10)</a></div>

