                    <div class="text post">
	
                        
                            <h2>The Waves Crashed Behind You</h2>
                        

                        <p>What if there&rsquo;s a star that spends its time watching my life, the years spread out like a cinema on their side of space? I wonder its waveform. I once swam in a bright green world, so let my sleep there induce a dream beautiful enough to keep, to rest, to stay stay stay.</p><p>I&rsquo;m not running away anymore. The night is still long, waiting for the robins to silence fear with a simple song. I&rsquo;ve walked under the darkness many times enough to invent some sort of melody. Come to me, let me love you, don&rsquo;t leave me, goodbye. Come to me, and walk the earth with me, don&rsquo;t leave me. I see a furious boy wading in the creek, trying to fill a jar with sunlit water, cursed to find its brightness forever fading in the dark.</p><p>It&rsquo;s deep inside of me&ndash; these questions that breathe in my heart&rsquo;s pasture, gently heaving blue from the sky. O the first place I ever loved is gone. They cut the trees down. O I just saw Jordan in the face of someone living. O and I saw the faces of friends replaced. I hope their ghosts never leave completely. O and I&rsquo;ve loved some people too desperately, and escaped their lives as demanded. I forgave, forgot. O the run, the run, the always running away. But let me ask: Can I be loved with my voice turned quiet? Will you love me with my voice turned quiet and my heart screaming? The sound so awfully loud&ndash; will you sit and listen with me? Will you speak back? Will you teach me this new language? Will you love a newer me? Say it. Please. Forever. It could be more than just a word.</p><p>Maybe someday I&rsquo;ll find a bright green world to live in. The autumn is shy, but I want years of fog pale November, and the never-ending waltz of white gale. No phantoms, but love quivering on every doorstep like evening light. Haunting, sometimes. Then there&rsquo;s us. You&rsquo;re whispering,&nbsp;&ldquo;stay,&rdquo; like you always do. I will. I always will.</p>
						
						<div class="postmeta"><a href="http://thenatureofdaylight.tumblr.com/post/150156118447/the-waves-crashed-behind-you">2 months ago</a>&nbsp; <a href="http://thenatureofdaylight.tumblr.com/post/150156118447/the-waves-crashed-behind-you" style="text-transform:lowercase;">Notes (2)</a></div>

