					</div>
					
                    <div class="text post">
	
                        
                            <h2>Your Eyes the Color of Inside the Earth</h2>
                        

                        <p>Sometimes the crows blend together with the sky just slightly enough that I don&rsquo;t see the life in our world. All of it. Unchanging. A train curls its tail, a fox curls its tail, and like I did 23 years ago, my body curls into sleep. And I&rsquo;ll hold, hold myself there till morning. My soul is not dream, but dreamer. And Delana is here dreaming with me.<br></p><p>I want to watch the fire burn the Earth someday in the summertime, and grow up in the fall. I&rsquo;ll fathom the sentences spilled from treetops and echoing branches, the space between I&rsquo;ll fall through, to the gentle carry, my thoughts, my journey, and waking up again in Delana&rsquo;s apartment, my hands spread on her back, carnation light pulling us to and from the windows to recite back the sacred sound. She loves, she loves me. Chorus alive in the distant roam of my ghosts, away outside, away years into the past. And here, my body a vapor dressing her, to listen to the sound. She loves me, she loves.</p><p>So call me when our moon swells and sobs, to drink the highlighter through the streets in our city. Never silent, never still, we drink the lights from the streets. Call me with your hands on the wheel, highway slowly delivering the memories of every home you&rsquo;ve ever had. All I ever wanted was something promised to me. The catch of your eyes and my story resounding. Reminding. I love, I love you.</p><p>Your name over the clouds, over the stars. 23 years, the oceans sail under time, above time, drowning time. It doesn&rsquo;t exist anymore. Why am I who I am? Could my body be more afraid of the earth? With skin thin enough you may sink inside? But two days ago the earth caught me from below, seaborne twines forming from deep inside, and so deep the music came. 

And there you were, your eyes repeating the same colors asleep inside of the earth. I love you Delana, kindled in midnight as the beach collapsed itself in love, like some pulse caught in my throat. Where is my life&rsquo;s thrum&ndash; but these waves and stars colliding? Do you feel them deeply in you too? I am, you are, I am, you are, I am, the water, the stars, now currents on the wind and carried, cast and carried away. And now I go everywhere with you.</p>
						
						<div class="postmeta"><a href="http://thenatureofdaylight.tumblr.com/post/150015172072/your-eyes-the-color-of-inside-the-earth">2 months ago</a>&nbsp; <a href="http://thenatureofdaylight.tumblr.com/post/150015172072/your-eyes-the-color-of-inside-the-earth" style="text-transform:lowercase;">Notes (2)</a></div>

